The following query searches for items named `laptop` and it sorts the
results by the `items.tags` field. The query includes a
[$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit) stage to limit the output to `5` documents and a
[$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage to:

- Exclude all fields except `items.name` and `items.tags`

- Add a field named `score`

**Input:**

```json
db.sales.aggregate({
  "$search": {
    "embeddedDocument": {
      "path": "items",
      "operator": {
        "text": {
          "path": "items.name",
          "query": "laptop"
        }
      }
    },
    "sort": {
      "items.tags": 1
    }
  }
},
{
  "$limit": 5
},
{
  "$project": {
    "_id": 0,
    "items.name": 1,
    "items.tags": 1,
    "score": { "$meta": "searchScore" }
